#!/usr/bin/perl

use App::Iops;
App::Iops->new( @ARGV )->run;
exit;

__END__

=head1 NAME

iops - Show process I/O operations

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  iops [options]

      --pid [pid]
      --help

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Summarize a process's I/O operations in real time.

Attach to an existing process:

  $ iops -p 3251
  read /dev/random...............................
  write /var/log/message..
  close /dev/random
